       <narrative xml:lang="EN">The collection of the best-available data and information is concluded in 2018. The data collected are stored in the Drin database in attribute tables rendering them usable by GIS tools. Further organization of the database will be necessary to render this usable by -external to the Project staff users- the institutions of the Riparians for their every-day work.A GIS portal (https://arcg.is/101H0n; work is on-going) providing georeferenced information and data has been prepared for the needs of the TDA development. Related information will feed in the IWLEARN geoinformation website (that is using Geonode). 
Six Thematic Reports comprise the analytical background of the TDA: (i) Pollution; (ii) Institutional and Legal Setting; (iii) Biodiversity and Ecosystems; (iv) Socioeconomics; (v) Hydrology/Hydrogeology; (vi) Water-Food-Energy-Ecosystems.
Nexus Thematic Report is prepared by UNECE with the assistance of four (4) National Experts, one for each Drin Riparian.  The thematic report is based on the results of the rest of the thematic reports. There is an effort, through this report and the Drin TDA, to combine, and if possible, to couple the TDA/SAP methodology with the Nexus assessment methodology. A concept note is developed by UNECE in cooperation with the Secretariat/PCU, presented to and approved by the 16th DCG / 7th SC meeting. The report is expected to be prepared in the first quarter 2019.</narrative>
